programme.desc:
Muskellunge fishing in New Brunswick
New Brunswick, Canada's Maritime Province, offers a variety of landscapes and aquatic habitats - making it the ideal destination for fishing enthusiasts. The province is known for its diverse list of sport fish, but one prized catch stands out from the rest: muskellunge.
Experienced anglers brave the cool waters of lakes, rivers and streams waiting to catch one of these aggressive fish. Although they can be difficult to locate, those who succeed are rewarded with an exciting fight and an impressive trophy worthy of display. Since freshwater muskies need an abundance of food to survive, techniques such as trolling with deep-diving crank baits or vertical jigging can be effective in catching this sought-after species.
Muskie fishing in New Brunswick offers experienced anglers a unique opportunity to test their skills and take on one of nature's top predators!
